ll wise men fear: the sea in storm, a night with no moon, and the anger of a gentle man.\n\n- Patrick Rothfuss, The Wise Man's Fear\n|\nBonding over illegal drugs hadn't magically solved our problems,\n\n- Shaun David Hutchinson, We Are the Ants\n|\nIt were better that we were not at all, than that we should live still in wickedness, and to suffer, and not to know wherefore.\n\n- Compton\n|\nThank you...for gracing my life with your lovely presence, for adding the sweet measure of your soul to my existence.\n\n- Richard Matheson, What Dreams May Come\n|\nConfession is always weakness. The grave soul keeps its own secrets, and takes its own punishment in silence.\n\n- Dorothy\n|\nFind the light within you through meditation and introspection, and you will illuminate your life from within.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, The Compassion Revolution: 30 Days of Living from the Heart\n|\nTurn the page, your heroine is still there, breathe, relax, life is beautiful: you're in a book!\n\n- Gabrielle\n|\nIf we wish for peace, we must pray for one another.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nThere will be another sky, my love, just you wait\n\n- Lori Nelson Spielman, The Life List\n|\nHow dare a person tell a woman, how to dress, how to talk, how to behave! Any being who does that, is no human.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Bengal Tigress: A Treatise on Gender Equality\n|\nYes: I am a dreamer. For a dreamer is one who can only find his way by moonlight, and his punishment is that he sees the dawn before the rest of the world.\n\n- Oscar Wilde, The Critic as Artist\n|\nThe basis of love that most people share is the intimacy they developed with their partners, the intensity of their attraction, or the similarity of their thought patterns,\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, Me Before Them\n|\nI have been writing now for over a week. I find it cleansing, refreshing; it is good for me.” (p.531)\n\n- Storm\n|\nComfort is not a goal that I seek, rather it is a place that I hide.\n\n- Craig\n|\nNo matter what the hatred 